net.proteusframework.ui.workspace

Interface Workspace

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Notifiable<Component>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    WorkspaceImpl

    public interface Workspace
extends Notifiable<Component>
    Workspace based UI interface.

    Workspace UIs are typically separated into several areas which include but are not limited to the following: selection area / search area, UI Task Management area, and UI Task View area.

    All interaction with the workspace happens through this interface.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

        Parameters:

      • addUITask

        void addUITask(UITask parent,
             UITask task)
        Add a UI task as a sub task to the specified parent. If the task is already present, the task is selected - it is not reparented. To reparent a task, the caller should call removeUITask(UITask) first. If you want to replace a task with another task with the same identifier, call first.
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent task to associated with the specified task.
        task - the task to add.
